(# FLUID Engineering Upgrade Plan) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## Purpose) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(This document defines how FLUID should evolve from a Chrome side-panel browser assistant into a) Tj T*
(practical engineering assistant that can investigate, fix, and verify real WordPress/support) Tj T*
(issues with evidence.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The target is not to copy hidden reasoning. The target is to copy the engineering workflow:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. Understand the user goal.) Tj T*
(2. Collect real evidence from browser, HTTP, files, logs, and tests.) Tj T*
(3. Decide the smallest safe fix.) Tj T*
(4. Apply changes only through the correct surface.) Tj T*
(5. Verify the result with repeatable checks.) Tj T*
(6. Save the lesson so the same failure does not repeat.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## Current State) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(FLUID currently has these working parts:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- Chrome sidebar extension in `extensions/chrome-sidebar`.) Tj T*
(- Local Node bridge in `tools/sidebar-bridge-node`.) Tj T*
(- Task checkpoint storage in `runs/bridge-tasks`.) Tj T*
(- Attachments storage in `runs/bridge-attachments`.) Tj T*
(- Provider contract that can return `reply`, `reasoning_summary`, `questions`, `actions`,) Tj T*
(`done`, and `needs_approval`.) Tj T*
(- Local planner in `tools/sidebar-bridge-node/src/local-planner.mjs`.) Tj T*
(- Provider router in `tools/sidebar-bridge-node/src/reasoner.mjs`.) Tj T*
(- Codex provider in `tools/sidebar-bridge-node/src/codex-provider.mjs`.) Tj T*
(- Unit tests in `tools/sidebar-bridge-node/test`.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Current limitation:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- The Chrome extension is good at page observation and browser actions.) Tj T*
(- The local planner is too keyword-driven for complex support work.) Tj T*
(- The bridge does not yet own full engineering tools such as filesystem inspection, shell) Tj T*
(commands, lint/test runs, Git checks, WordPress HTTP sessions, or structured verification.) Tj T*
(- It can act in the browser, but it cannot yet reliably do full root-cause investigation) Tj T*
(without help.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## Extension Vs Desktop Decision) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Do not move everything into the Chrome extension.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Use a hybrid architecture:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(```text) Tj T*
(Chrome Sidebar) Tj T*
(  - user interface) Tj T*
(  - current tab snapshot) Tj T*
(  - screenshots) Tj T*
ET
endstream
endobj
