(  - PR-gated self improvement) Tj T*
(```) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Reason:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Chrome extensions are sandboxed. They should not directly edit local files, run shell commands,) Tj T*
(lint PHP, inspect Git history, or deploy changes. The bridge can do those things with explicit) Tj T*
(safety gates.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## Main Design Rule) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(FLUID must never jump from user text directly to a fix.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Every non-trivial task must follow this loop:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(```text) Tj T*
(Goal -> Evidence -> Hypothesis -> Fix Plan -> Approval Gate -> Patch -> Verification -> Lesson) Tj T*
(```) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(If evidence is missing, FLUID must ask a short question or run a safe observation step.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## Required Work Modes) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(### 1. Browser Mode) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Use when the task is only browser navigation or visible page checking.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Allowed actions:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(- navigate) Tj T*
(- click) Tj T*
(- type) Tj T*
(- press) Tj T*
(- wait) Tj T*
(- observe) Tj T*
(- screenshot) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Browser Mode must stop before:) Tj T*
ET
endstream
endobj
